headline: A Look At State Street (STT) Valuation After Earnings Beat And Digital Expansion Updates
summary: State Street (STT) is back in focus after fourth quarter 2025 results topped analyst revenue and earnings expectations, even as the share price slipped more than 4% on the news. See our latest analysis for State Street. That drop in response to earnings comes after a steadier climb, with the 90 day share price return of 8.59% and a 1 year total shareholder return of 31.10% pointing to momentum that has cooled in the past month as investors reassess recent launches in digital assets, private...
